<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Riddle</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-10"><hi rend="italic">May 10,
                                1906</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 12, Servian Series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith, for appropriate
                            inquiry and report, a copy of a letter<note n="a" xml:id="d428fna">Not
                                printed.</note> from Mr. Milorad J. Pavlovitch, a naturalized
                            citizen of the United States of Servian origin, relative to the matter
                            of the collection from his parents of an army tax.</p>
                        <p>You will return the original receipt transmitted with Mr. Pavlovitch’s
                            letter after it shall have served the purpose for which it is sent.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>